joke: Why did the coffee file a police report? It got mugged.
What’s a computer’s favorite snack? Microchips.
Why don’t mountains ever get tired? They peak all the time.
What do you call a sleeping dinosaur? A dino-snore.
Why did the soccer player bring string? To tie the score.
Why did the flashlight go to school? It wanted to be a little brighter.
What do you call an angry carrot? A steamed veggie.
Why don’t bakers ever get stressed? They just loaf around.
How do you fix a broken tomato? With tomato paste.
Why did the smartphone need glasses? It lost its contacts.
What do you call a fake noodle? An impasta.
Why don’t trees take tests? They always branch out.
What did the elevator say to the stairs? You’re always bringing me down.
Why did the cow become an astronaut? It wanted to see the moooon!
Why did the belt go to jail? It was holding up a pair of pants!
Why do fish never do well in school? They work below sea level.
Why don’t ghosts like rain? It dampens their spirits.
What do you call a happy cowboy? A jolly rancher.
Why don’t fireflies play hide and seek? Because they glow it!
Why do bicycles stay upright? Because they’re two-tired to fall!
